bio.title: Full-Stack Developer & AI Enthusiast
bio.summary: Natinael is a versatile full-stack developer with 4+ years of experience building scalable web applications and AI-powered solutions. He specializes in the MERN stack and has successfully led multiple projects from concept to deployment. His unique blend of technical expertise, entrepreneurial mindset, and business acumen allows him to create solutions that address real-world problems effectively.

projects.title: MyFayda eKYC
projects.description: MyFayda eKYC is a digital identity solution that integrates with the Fayda National ID system, empowering users to verify their identities securely. It aims to enhance trust in digital services and support the growth of a digital economy in Ethiopia.
accomplishments: Integrated with national ID system for secure identity verification
Built scalable authentication system serving thousands of users
Implemented responsive UI with Tailwind CSS

projects.title: MedHub Ethiopia
projects.description: MedHub Ethiopia is the first Electronic Medical Record (EMR) system in Ethiopia, designed to streamline patient management for healthcare providers. It integrates with the national ID system, enhancing the efficiency and reliability of healthcare services.
accomplishments: Developed Ethiopia's first EMR system with national ID integration
Implemented secure patient data management compliant with healthcare regulations
Built telemedicine capabilities using WebRTC

projects.title: Academic Assignment Helper & Plagiarism Detector (RAG-Powered)
projects.description: An AI-driven academic assistant that integrates Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) with plagiarism detection and automated assignment submission. The system extracts assignment content, performs semantic similarity search using vector embeddings, evaluates plagiarism, summarizes results via Friendli AI, and automates student notifications through n8n email workflows.
accomplishments: Implemented full RAG-based AI analysis pipeline integrating plagiarism detection and contextual summarization.
Built a background AI processing module using FastAPI and Friendli AI endpoints with retry and JSON sanitization.
Designed n8n automation flows for real-time student feedback and instructor notifications with dynamic email HTML.
Enabled automatic academic source embedding, vector indexing, and context-aware retrieval using FAISS.
Developed an optional automated submission system that sends plagiarism-free proof and analysis to instructors.
